name: Bulbasaur
pokedex_entry: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

name: Ivysaur
pokedex_entry: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

name: Venusaur
pokedex_entry: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Charmander
pokedex_entry: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

name: Charmeleon
pokedex_entry: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

name: Charizard
pokedex_entry: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

name: Squirtle
pokedex_entry: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

name: Wartortle
pokedex_entry: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

name: Blastoise
pokedex_entry: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Caterpie
pokedex_entry: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

name: Metapod
pokedex_entry: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

name: Butterfree
pokedex_entry: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

name: Weedle
pokedex_entry: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

name: Kakuna
pokedex_entry: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.

name: Beedrill
pokedex_entry: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

name: Pidgey
abilities: Keen Eye, Tangled Feet, Big Pecks
pokedex_entry: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Pidgeotto
abilities: Keen Eye, Tangled Feet, Big Pecks
pokedex_entry: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.

name: Pidgeot
abilities: Keen Eye, Tangled Feet, Big Pecks
pokedex_entry: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

name: Rattata
pokedex_entry: Its incisors continue growing until its death. If its Trainer doesn’t offer it a file to gnaw on, it will gnaw on door frames, table legs, and so on.

name: Raticate
pokedex_entry: Its hind feet are webbed, so it’s a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.

name: Spearow
pokedex_entry: Its short wings make it inept at flying. It moves about hurriedly and pecks at Bug-type Pokémon in the tall grass.

name: Fearow
pokedex_entry: It’s tough and has excellent stamina. It has no problem flying continuously for a whole day carrying a heavy load.

name: Ekans
pokedex_entry: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

name: Arbok
pokedex_entry: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

name: Pikachu
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Raichu
pokedex_entry: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

name: Sandshrew
pokedex_entry: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

name: Sandslash
pokedex_entry: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon’s spikes will feel when touched.

name: Nidoran F
pokedex_entry: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they’ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

name: Nidorina
pokedex_entry: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.

name: Nidoqueen
pokedex_entry: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

name: Nidoran M
pokedex_entry: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

name: Nidorino
pokedex_entry: With a horn that’s harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

name: Nidoking
pokedex_entry: When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

name: Clefairy
abilities: Cute Charm, Magic Guard, Friend Guard
pokedex_entry: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

name: Clefable
pokedex_entry: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

name: Vulpix
pokedex_entry: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales
pokedex_entry: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

name: Jigglypuff
pokedex_entry: Jigglypuff has top-notch lung capacity, even by comparison to other Pokémon. It won’t stop singing its lullabies until its foes fall asleep.

name: Wigglytuff
pokedex_entry: The more air it takes in, the more it inflates. If opponents catch it in a bad mood, it will inflate itself to an enormous size to intimidate them.

name: Zubat
pokedex_entry: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

name: Golbat
pokedex_entry: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

name: Oddish
pokedex_entry: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
pokedex_entry: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Vileplume
pokedex_entry: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

name: Paras
pokedex_entry: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

name: Parasect
pokedex_entry: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

name: Venonat
abilities: Compound Eyes, Tinted Lens, Run Away
pokedex_entry: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

name: Venomoth
abilities: Shield Dust, Tinted Lens, Wonder Skin
pokedex_entry: The scales it scatters will paralyze anyone who touches them, making that person unable to stand.

name: Diglett
abilities: Sand Veil, Arena Trap, Sand Force
pokedex_entry: If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

name: Dugtrio
abilities: Sand Veil, Arena Trap, Sand Force
pokedex_entry: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

name: Meowth
pokedex_entry: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

name: Persian
pokedex_entry: Getting this prideful Pokémon to warm up to you takes a lot of effort, and it will claw at you the moment it gets annoyed.

name: Psyduck
pokedex_entry: Psyduck is constantly beset by headaches. If the Pokémon lets its strange power erupt, apparently the pain subsides for a while.

name: Golduck
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

name: Mankey
pokedex_entry: It can spontaneously become enraged. Everyone near it clears out as it rampages, and the resulting loneliness makes it angrier still.

name: Primeape
pokedex_entry: It has been known to become so angry that it dies as a result. Its face looks peaceful in death, however.

name: Growlithe
pokedex_entry: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
pokedex_entry: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

name: Poliwag
pokedex_entry: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

name: Poliwhirl
pokedex_entry: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

name: Poliwrath
pokedex_entry: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

name: Abra
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

name: Kadabra
pokedex_entry: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

name: Alakazam
pokedex_entry: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Machop
pokedex_entry: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
pokedex_entry: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

name: Machamp
pokedex_entry: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Bellsprout
pokedex_entry: Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

name: Weepinbell
pokedex_entry: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

name: Victreebel
pokedex_entry: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

name: Tentacool
abilities: Clear Body, Liquid Ooze, Rain Dish
pokedex_entry: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

name: Tentacruel
abilities: Clear Body, Liquid Ooze, Rain Dish
pokedex_entry: When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

name: Geodude
pokedex_entry: Its round body makes it easy to pick up, but it is hard and heavy. It’s dangerous to play with them as if they were snowballs.

name: Graveler
pokedex_entry: Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly.

name: Golem
pokedex_entry: Its body can survive dynamite blasts without a single scratch, but it hates rain and humidity.

name: Ponyta
abilities: Run Away, Flash Fire, Flame Body
pokedex_entry: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

name: Rapidash
abilities: Run Away, Flash Fire, Flame Body
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Slowpoke
pokedex_entry: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won’t feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won’t notice when its tail grows back, either.

name: Slowbro
pokedex_entry: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

name: Magnemite
pokedex_entry: At times, Magnemite runs out of electricity and ends up on the ground. If you give batteries to a grounded Magnemite, it’ll start moving again.

name: Magneton
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.

name: Farfetchd
pokedex_entry: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Doduo
abilities: Run Away, Early Bird, Tangled Feet
pokedex_entry: A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

name: Dodrio
abilities: Run Away, Early Bird, Tangled Feet
pokedex_entry: An enemy that takes its eyes off any of the three heads--even for a second--will get pecked severely.

name: Seel
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.

name: Dewgong
pokedex_entry: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.

name: Grimer
pokedex_entry: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokémon’s numbers have been decreasing in recent years.

name: Muk
pokedex_entry: The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that’s a good thing.

name: Shellder
pokedex_entry: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

name: Cloyster
pokedex_entry: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

name: Gastly
pokedex_entry: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

name: Haunter
pokedex_entry: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

name: Gengar
pokedex_entry: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar’s doing.

name: Onix
pokedex_entry: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

name: Drowzee
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon that nourishes itself by eating dreams, it is thought to share common ancestry with Munna and Musharna.

name: Hypno
pokedex_entry: While it is an extremely dangerous Pokémon, people who are in need of a good, sound sleep call it their savior.

name: Krabby
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Shell Armor, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

name: Kingler
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Shell Armor, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

name: Voltorb
pokedex_entry: It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.

name: Electrode
pokedex_entry: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of “The Bomb Ball.”

name: Exeggcute
pokedex_entry: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Exeggutor
pokedex_entry: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

name: Cubone
abilities: Rock Head, Lightning Rod, Battle Armor
pokedex_entry: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

name: Marowak
abilities: Rock Head, Lightning Rod, Battle Armor
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

name: Hitmonlee
pokedex_entry: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

name: Hitmonchan
abilities: Keen Eye, Iron Fist, Inner Focus
pokedex_entry: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

name: Lickitung
pokedex_entry: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Koffing
pokedex_entry: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

name: Weezing
pokedex_entry: It mixes gases between its two bodies. It’s said that these Pokémon were seen all over the Galar region back in the day.

name: Rhyhorn
pokedex_entry: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

name: Rhydon
pokedex_entry: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Chansey
pokedex_entry: The egg Chansey carries is not only delicious but also packed with nutrition. It’s used as a high-class cooking ingredient.

name: Tangela
pokedex_entry: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Kangaskhan
pokedex_entry: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

name: Horsea
pokedex_entry: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

name: Seadra
pokedex_entry: It’s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

name: Goldeen
abilities: Swift Swim, Water Veil, Lightning Rod
pokedex_entry: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

name: Seaking
abilities: Swift Swim, Water Veil, Lightning Rod
pokedex_entry: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

name: Staryu
pokedex_entry: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

name: Starmie
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

name: Mr Mime
pokedex_entry: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Scyther
pokedex_entry: As Scyther fights more and more battles, its scythes become sharper and sharper. With a single slice, Scyther can fell a massive tree.

name: Jynx
pokedex_entry: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.

name: Electabuzz
pokedex_entry: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Magmar
pokedex_entry: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

name: Pinsir
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Tauros
pokedex_entry: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Magikarp
pokedex_entry: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.

name: Gyarados
pokedex_entry: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

name: Lapras
pokedex_entry: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Ditto
pokedex_entry: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

name: Eevee
pokedex_entry: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

name: Vaporeon
pokedex_entry: When Vaporeon’s fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

name: Jolteon
pokedex_entry: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

name: Flareon
pokedex_entry: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon’s body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
pokedex_entry: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

name: Omanyte
abilities: Swift Swim, Shell Armor, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.

name: Omastar
abilities: Swift Swim, Shell Armor, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn’t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

name: Kabuto
abilities: Swift Swim, Battle Armor, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

name: Kabutops
abilities: Swift Swim, Battle Armor, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

name: Aerodactyl
pokedex_entry: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

name: Snorlax
pokedex_entry: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Articuno
pokedex_entry: It’s said that this Pokémon’s beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

name: Zapdos
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

name: Moltres
pokedex_entry: It’s one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

name: Dratini
pokedex_entry: Dratini dwells near bodies of rapidly flowing water, such as the plunge pools of waterfalls. As it grows, Dratini will shed its skin many times.

name: Dragonair
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon lives in pristine oceans and lakes. It can control the weather, and it uses this power to fly into the sky, riding on the wind.

name: Dragonite
pokedex_entry: It’s a kindhearted Pokémon. If it spots a drowning person or Pokémon, Dragonite simply must help them.

name: Mewtwo
pokedex_entry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

name: Mew
pokedex_entry: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

name: Chikorita
pokedex_entry: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up sun rays.

name: Bayleef
pokedex_entry: A spicy aroma emanates from around its neck. The aroma acts as a stimulant to restore health.

name: Meganium
pokedex_entry: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.

name: Cyndaquil
pokedex_entry: It is timid and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.

name: Quilava
pokedex_entry: Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.

name: Typhlosion
pokedex_entry: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

name: Totodile
pokedex_entry: It is small but rough and tough. It won’t hesitate to take a bite out of anything that moves.

name: Croconaw
pokedex_entry: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

name: Feraligatr
pokedex_entry: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

name: Sentret
pokedex_entry: When acting as a lookout, it warns others of danger by screeching and hitting the ground with its tail.

name: Furret
pokedex_entry: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

name: Hoothoot
pokedex_entry: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

name: Noctowl
pokedex_entry: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

name: Ledyba
pokedex_entry: They are timid and grow uneasy when not in a swarm with others of their kind. The pattern on their backs differs slightly from one to another.

name: Ledian
pokedex_entry: While it’s believed that starlight provides it with energy, this Pokémon also loves to eat berries. In the daytime, it curls up in the grass to sleep.

name: Spinarak
pokedex_entry: It waits intently until its preferred prey, Cutiefly, gets caught in its web. In fact, it’s quite a patient Pokémon.

name: Ariados
pokedex_entry: There are some areas where people use the string Ariados spins for their own weaving. The resulting cloth is popular for its strength.

name: Crobat
pokedex_entry: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.

name: Chinchou
pokedex_entry: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

name: Lanturn
pokedex_entry: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea’s surface from a depth of over three miles.

name: Pichu
pokedex_entry: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

name: Cleffa
abilities: Cute Charm, Magic Guard, Friend Guard
pokedex_entry: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

name: Igglybuff
pokedex_entry: Igglybuff loves to sing. Its marshmallow-like body gives off a faint sweet smell.

name: Togepi
pokedex_entry: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Togetic
pokedex_entry: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

name: Natu
pokedex_entry: It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.

name: Xatu
pokedex_entry: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

name: Mareep
pokedex_entry: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

name: Flaaffy
pokedex_entry: Its fluffy fleece easily stores electricity. Its rubbery hide keeps it from being electrocuted.

name: Ampharos
pokedex_entry: The tail’s tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Bellossom
pokedex_entry: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

name: Marill
abilities: Thick Fat, Huge Power, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon uses its round tail as a float. The ball of Marill’s tail is filled with nutrients that have been turned into an oil.

name: Azumarill
abilities: Thick Fat, Huge Power, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: It spends most of its time in the water. On sunny days, Azumarill floats on the surface of the water and sunbathes.

name: Sudowoodo
pokedex_entry: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it’s a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.

name: Politoed
pokedex_entry: At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

name: Hoppip
pokedex_entry: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

name: Skiploom
pokedex_entry: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.

name: Jumpluff
pokedex_entry: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

name: Aipom
pokedex_entry: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

name: Sunkern
pokedex_entry: It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.

name: Sunflora
pokedex_entry: As the hot season approaches, the petals on this Pokémon’s face become more vivid and lively.

name: Yanma
pokedex_entry: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won’t miss prey--even those behind it.

name: Wooper
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Quagsire
pokedex_entry: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

name: Espeon
pokedex_entry: By reading air currents, it can predict things such as the weather or its foe’s next move.

name: Umbreon
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon becomes angry, its pores secrete a poisonous sweat, which it sprays at its opponent’s eyes.

name: Murkrow
pokedex_entry: They awaken at dusk and take wing in the twilight, leading to the expression, “Get home before the Murkrow fly.”

name: Slowking
pokedex_entry: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke’s latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

name: Misdreavus
pokedex_entry: It will use any means necessary to frighten people and absorb their life energy. It practices constantly to hone its skill in causing fear.

name: Unown
pokedex_entry: Its flat, thin body is always stuck on walls. Its shape appears to have some meaning.

name: Wobbuffet
pokedex_entry: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

name: Girafarig
abilities: Inner Focus, Early Bird, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: While it sleeps, the head on its tail keeps watch. The tail doesn’t need to sleep.

name: Pineco
pokedex_entry: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn’t bother it.

name: Forretress
pokedex_entry: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

name: Dunsparce
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon’s tiny wings have some scientists saying that Dunsparce used to fly through the sky in ancient times.

name: Gligar
pokedex_entry: It usually clings to cliffs. When it spots its prey, it spreads its wings and glides down to attack.

name: Steelix
pokedex_entry: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

name: Snubbull
pokedex_entry: Despite its intimidating face, it’s quite cowardly. Its desperate attempts to appear threatening make it popular with people.

name: Granbull
pokedex_entry: Its well-developed lower jaw and heavy fangs are its weapons. As long as it’s not provoked, it rarely bites.

name: Qwilfish
pokedex_entry: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent’s size.

name: Scizor
pokedex_entry: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor’s body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

name: Shuckle
pokedex_entry: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

name: Heracross
pokedex_entry: Heracross loves sweet sap and will go looking through forests for it. The Pokémon uses its two antennae to pick up scents as it searches.

name: Sneasel
pokedex_entry: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

name: Teddiursa
pokedex_entry: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they’re soaked with honey.

name: Ursaring
pokedex_entry: With its ability to distinguish any aroma, it unfailingly finds all food buried deep underground.

name: Slugma
abilities: Magma Armor, Flame Body, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

name: Magcargo
abilities: Magma Armor, Flame Body, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

name: Swinub
pokedex_entry: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine
pokedex_entry: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Corsola
pokedex_entry: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

name: Remoraid
pokedex_entry: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

name: Octillery
pokedex_entry: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

name: Delibird
pokedex_entry: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

name: Mantine
abilities: Swift Swim, Water Absorb, Water Veil
pokedex_entry: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

name: Skarmory
pokedex_entry: The pointed feathers of these Pokémon are sharper than swords. Skarmory and Corviknight fight viciously over territory.

name: Houndour
pokedex_entry: Around dawn, its ominous howl echoes through the area to announce that this is its territory.

name: Houndoom
pokedex_entry: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

name: Kingdra
pokedex_entry: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

name: Phanpy
pokedex_entry: As a sign of affection, it bumps with its snout. However, it is so strong, it may send you flying.

name: Donphan
pokedex_entry: It has sharp, hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its Tackle is strong enough to knock down a house.

name: Porygon2
pokedex_entry: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

name: Stantler
pokedex_entry: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

name: Smeargle
pokedex_entry: The unique creations produced by each Smeargle are painted using the fluid that oozes from its tail. This is how it marks its territory.

name: Tyrogue
pokedex_entry: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

name: Hitmontop
pokedex_entry: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Smoochum
pokedex_entry: If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty, Smoochum doesn’t really seem to care.

name: Elekid
pokedex_entry: When a storm approaches, this Pokémon gets restless. Once Elekid hears the sound of thunder, it gets full-on rowdy.

name: Magby
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is still small and timid. Whenever Magby gets excited or surprised, flames leak from its mouth and its nose.

name: Miltank
pokedex_entry: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

name: Blissey
pokedex_entry: Whenever a Blissey finds a weakened Pokémon, it will share its egg and offer its care until the other Pokémon is all better.

name: Raikou
pokedex_entry: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

name: Entei
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

name: Suicune
pokedex_entry: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

name: Larvitar
pokedex_entry: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

name: Pupitar
pokedex_entry: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

name: Tyranitar
pokedex_entry: Its body can’t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

name: Lugia
pokedex_entry: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

name: Ho Oh
pokedex_entry: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

name: Celebi
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.

name: Treecko
pokedex_entry: It quickly scales even vertical walls. It senses humidity with its tail to predict the next day’s weather.

name: Grovyle
pokedex_entry: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.

name: Sceptile
pokedex_entry: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

name: Torchic
pokedex_entry: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

name: Combusken
pokedex_entry: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

name: Blaziken
pokedex_entry: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

name: Mudkip
pokedex_entry: Its large tail fin propels it through water with powerful acceleration. It is strong in spite of its size.

name: Marshtomp
pokedex_entry: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

name: Swampert
pokedex_entry: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break a boulder into pieces.

name: Poochyena
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Mightyena
pokedex_entry: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

name: Zigzagoon
pokedex_entry: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

name: Linoone
pokedex_entry: Its fur is strong and supple. Shaving brushes made with shed Linoone hairs are highly prized.

name: Wurmple
pokedex_entry: It loves to eat leaves. If it is attacked by a Starly, it will defend itself with its spiked rear.

name: Silcoon
pokedex_entry: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

name: Beautifly
pokedex_entry: Vibrantly patterned wings are its prominent feature. It sucks sweet flower nectar with its long mouth.

name: Cascoon
pokedex_entry: Its body, which is made of soft silk, hardens over time. When cracks appear, evolution is near.

name: Dustox
pokedex_entry: A nocturnal Pokémon. Drawn by streetlights, they messily eat the leaves of trees lining boulevards.

name: Lotad
abilities: Swift Swim, Rain Dish, Own Tempo
pokedex_entry: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

name: Lombre
abilities: Swift Swim, Rain Dish, Own Tempo
pokedex_entry: It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.

name: Ludicolo
abilities: Swift Swim, Rain Dish, Own Tempo
pokedex_entry: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo’s cells, making it more powerful.

name: Seedot
pokedex_entry: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

name: Nuzleaf
pokedex_entry: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe’s mind and take preemptive action.

name: Taillow
pokedex_entry: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

name: Swellow
pokedex_entry: If its two tail feathers are standing at attention, it is proof of good health. It soars elegantly in the sky.

name: Wingull
pokedex_entry: It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.

name: Pelipper
pokedex_entry: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

name: Ralts
pokedex_entry: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

name: Kirlia
pokedex_entry: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

name: Gardevoir
pokedex_entry: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.

name: Surskit
pokedex_entry: It moves as if skating on the surface of the water. It often fights with Dewpider over food.

name: Masquerain
pokedex_entry: It intimidates enemies with the eye-like patterns on its antennae. Its four wings allow it to fly in any direction.

name: Shroomish
abilities: Effect Spore, Poison Heal, Quick Feet
pokedex_entry: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

name: Breloom
pokedex_entry: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

name: Slakoth
pokedex_entry: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.

name: Vigoroth
pokedex_entry: Its heartbeat is fast and its blood so agitated that it can’t sit still for one second.

name: Slaking
pokedex_entry: The world’s laziest Pokémon. It moves to another spot when there’s no food left within its reach.

name: Nincada
pokedex_entry: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.

name: Ninjask
pokedex_entry: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

name: Shedinja
pokedex_entry: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.

name: Whismur
pokedex_entry: The cry of a Whismur is over 100 decibels. If you’re close to a Whismur when it lets out a cry, you’ll be stuck with an all-day headache.

name: Loudred
pokedex_entry: Loudred’s ears serve as speakers, and they can put out sound waves powerful enough to blow away a house.

name: Exploud
pokedex_entry: In the past, people would use the loud voices of these Pokémon as a means of communication between distant cities.

name: Makuhita
pokedex_entry: It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.

name: Hariyama
pokedex_entry: It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training Makuhita.

name: Azurill
abilities: Thick Fat, Huge Power, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: The ball on Azurill’s tail bounces like a rubber ball, and it’s full of the nutrients the Pokémon needs to grow.

name: Nosepass
pokedex_entry: The magnet in Nosepass’s nose provides an unerring compass, making it an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

name: Skitty
pokedex_entry: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

name: Delcatty
pokedex_entry: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Sableye
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it’s believed that Sableye will steal people’s spirits away.

name: Mawile
pokedex_entry: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

name: Aron
pokedex_entry: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

name: Lairon
pokedex_entry: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

name: Aggron
pokedex_entry: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

name: Meditite
pokedex_entry: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.

name: Medicham
pokedex_entry: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Electrike
pokedex_entry: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

name: Manectric
pokedex_entry: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.

name: Plusle
pokedex_entry: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

name: Minun
pokedex_entry: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.

name: Volbeat
pokedex_entry: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise’s sweet aroma.

name: Illumise
pokedex_entry: Its fragrance attracts a swarm of Volbeat, so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.

name: Roselia
abilities: Natural Cure, Poison Point, Leaf Guard
pokedex_entry: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

name: Gulpin
pokedex_entry: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.

name: Swalot
pokedex_entry: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

name: Carvanha
pokedex_entry: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

name: Sharpedo
pokedex_entry: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

name: Wailmer
pokedex_entry: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

name: Wailord
pokedex_entry: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

name: Numel
pokedex_entry: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.

name: Camerupt
abilities: Magma Armor, Solid Rock, Anger Point
pokedex_entry: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.

name: Torkoal
pokedex_entry: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

name: Spoink
pokedex_entry: It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.

name: Grumpig
pokedex_entry: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.

name: Spinda
pokedex_entry: Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it’s walking in a straight line.

name: Trapinch
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Arena Trap, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

name: Vibrava
pokedex_entry: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.

name: Flygon
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

name: Cacnea
pokedex_entry: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

name: Cacturne
pokedex_entry: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day’s desert heat.

name: Swablu
pokedex_entry: Its cottony wings are full of air, making them light and fluffy to the touch. Swablu takes diligent care of its wings.

name: Altaria
pokedex_entry: As it flies in a calm and relaxed manner, Altaria performs a humming song that would enrapture any audience.

name: Zangoose
pokedex_entry: It has feuded with Seviper for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.

name: Seviper
pokedex_entry: In battle, it uses its bladed tail to counter any Zangoose. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.

name: Lunatone
pokedex_entry: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

name: Solrock
pokedex_entry: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

name: Barboach
pokedex_entry: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

name: Whiscash
pokedex_entry: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

name: Corphish
pokedex_entry: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

name: Crawdaunt
pokedex_entry: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

name: Baltoy
pokedex_entry: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.

name: Claydol
pokedex_entry: This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.

name: Lileep
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

name: Cradily
pokedex_entry: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

name: Anorith
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.

name: Armaldo
pokedex_entry: After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.

name: Feebas
pokedex_entry: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon’s marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

name: Milotic
pokedex_entry: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

name: Castform
pokedex_entry: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

name: Kecleon
pokedex_entry: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.

name: Shuppet
pokedex_entry: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice-- or so it’s said. It’s very active at night.

name: Banette
pokedex_entry: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.

name: Duskull
pokedex_entry: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it’s said.

name: Dusclops
pokedex_entry: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.

name: Tropius
pokedex_entry: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.

name: Chimecho
pokedex_entry: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.

name: Absol
pokedex_entry: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Wynaut
pokedex_entry: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

name: Snorunt
pokedex_entry: It’s said that if they are seen at midnight, they’ll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.

name: Glalie
pokedex_entry: It has a body of ice that won’t melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.

name: Spheal
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon’s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It’s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

name: Sealeo
pokedex_entry: Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they’re on the hunt, seeking out their prey by scent.

name: Walrein
pokedex_entry: Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears, the herd’s leader will protect the group with its life.

name: Clamperl
pokedex_entry: When it evolves, it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it’s held.

name: Huntail
pokedex_entry: It lives deep in the sea where no light ever filters down. It lights up its small fishlike tail to attract prey.

name: Gorebyss
pokedex_entry: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

name: Relicanth
pokedex_entry: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

name: Luvdisc
pokedex_entry: If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when Pelipper snatch them up.

name: Bagon
pokedex_entry: Bagon jumps off cliffs every day, trying to grow stronger so that someday it will be able to fly.

name: Shelgon
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has covered its body in a hard shell that has the same composition as bone. Shelgon stores energy for evolution.

name: Salamence
pokedex_entry: Salamence is an unusual Pokémon in that it was able to evolve a body with wings just by constantly wishing to be able to fly.

name: Beldum
pokedex_entry: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum’s sharp claws.

name: Metang
pokedex_entry: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

name: Metagross
pokedex_entry: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

name: Regirock
pokedex_entry: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

name: Regice
pokedex_entry: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

name: Registeel
pokedex_entry: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.

name: Latias
pokedex_entry: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Latios
pokedex_entry: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

name: Kyogre
pokedex_entry: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.

name: Groudon
pokedex_entry: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.

name: Rayquaza
pokedex_entry: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: Jirachi
pokedex_entry: Once every 1,000 years, the singing of a pure voice will rouse this Pokémon from its near- perpetual slumber. It wakes for only seven days.

name: Deoxys Normal
pokedex_entry: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Turtwig
pokedex_entry: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

name: Grotle
pokedex_entry: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: Torterra
pokedex_entry: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.

name: Chimchar
pokedex_entry: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

name: Monferno
pokedex_entry: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

name: Infernape
pokedex_entry: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: Piplup
pokedex_entry: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
pokedex_entry: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

name: Empoleon
pokedex_entry: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

name: Starly
pokedex_entry: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: Staravia
pokedex_entry: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

name: Staraptor
pokedex_entry: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.

name: Bidoof
pokedex_entry: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: Bibarel
pokedex_entry: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

name: Kricketot
pokedex_entry: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

name: Kricketune
pokedex_entry: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

name: Shinx
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

name: Luxio
pokedex_entry: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokémon can receive some of the other Luxio’s electricity and power up its own electric blasts.

name: Luxray
pokedex_entry: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.

name: Budew
abilities: Natural Cure, Poison Point, Leaf Guard
pokedex_entry: The pollen it releases contains poison. If this Pokémon is raised on clean water, the poison’s toxicity is increased.

name: Roserade
pokedex_entry: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

name: Cranidos
pokedex_entry: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.

name: Rampardos
pokedex_entry: The result of repeated headbutts is a skull grown thick and hard. However, its brain has shrunk in size compared with Cranidos’s.

name: Shieldon
pokedex_entry: Many fossils of this Pokémon have been found, but almost none have shown signs of damage to the face.

name: Bastiodon
pokedex_entry: While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front, it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.

name: Burmy
pokedex_entry: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Wormadam Plant
pokedex_entry: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Mothim
pokedex_entry: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

name: Combee
pokedex_entry: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.

name: Vespiquen
pokedex_entry: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.

name: Pachirisu
pokedex_entry: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: Buizel
pokedex_entry: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

name: Floatzel
pokedex_entry: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: Cherubi
pokedex_entry: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.

name: Cherrim
pokedex_entry: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.

name: Shellos
abilities: Sticky Hold, Storm Drain, Sand Force
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon’s habitat shapes its physique. According to some theories, life in warm ocean waters causes this variation to develop.

name: Gastrodon
abilities: Sticky Hold, Storm Drain, Sand Force
pokedex_entry: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.

name: Ambipom
pokedex_entry: They work in large colonies and make rings by linking their tails, apparently in friendship.

name: Drifloon
pokedex_entry: Perhaps seeking company, it approaches children. However, it often quickly runs away again when the children play too roughly with it.

name: Drifblim
pokedex_entry: Some say this Pokémon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.

name: Buneary
pokedex_entry: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokémon is in need of care.

name: Lopunny
pokedex_entry: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

name: Mismagius
pokedex_entry: It appears as if from nowhere—muttering incantations, placing curses, and giving people terrifying visions.

name: Honchkrow
pokedex_entry: A single cry from this nocturnal Pokémon, and more than a hundred of its Murkrow cronies will assemble.

name: Glameow
pokedex_entry: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Purugly
pokedex_entry: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

name: Chingling
pokedex_entry: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

name: Stunky
pokedex_entry: From its rear, it sprays a foul-smelling liquid at opponents. It aims for their faces, and it can hit them from over 16 feet away.

name: Skuntank
pokedex_entry: In its belly, it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots from its tail during battle. As this Pokémon’s diet varies, so does the stench of its fluid.

name: Bronzor
pokedex_entry: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn’t come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.

name: Bronzong
pokedex_entry: Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.

name: Bonsly
pokedex_entry: It expels both sweat and tears from its eyes. The sweat is a little salty, while the tears have a slight bitterness.

name: Mime Jr
pokedex_entry: It mimics everyone it sees, but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

name: Happiny
abilities: Natural Cure, Serene Grace, Friend Guard
pokedex_entry: Mimicking Chansey, Happiny will place an egg- shaped stone in its belly pouch. Happiny will treasure this stone.

name: Chatot
abilities: Keen Eye, Tangled Feet, Big Pecks
pokedex_entry: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

name: Spiritomb
pokedex_entry: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.

name: Gible
pokedex_entry: Gible prefers to stay in narrow holes in the sides of caves heated by geothermal energy. This way, Gible can stay warm even during a blizzard.

name: Gabite
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.

name: Garchomp
pokedex_entry: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.

name: Munchlax
pokedex_entry: Stuffing itself with vast amounts of food is its only concern. Whether the food is rotten or fresh, yummy or tasteless—it does not care.

name: Riolu
pokedex_entry: It’s exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

name: Lucario
pokedex_entry: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.

name: Hippopotas
pokedex_entry: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.

name: Hippowdon
pokedex_entry: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.

name: Skorupi
pokedex_entry: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

name: Drapion
pokedex_entry: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

name: Croagunk
pokedex_entry: It makes frightening noises with its poison-filled cheek sacs. When opponents flinch, Croagunk hits them with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak
pokedex_entry: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.

name: Carnivine
pokedex_entry: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Finneon
abilities: Swift Swim, Storm Drain, Water Veil
pokedex_entry: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.

name: Lumineon
abilities: Swift Swim, Storm Drain, Water Veil
pokedex_entry: With its shining light, it lures its prey close. However, the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokémon—its natural predators.

name: Mantyke
abilities: Swift Swim, Water Absorb, Water Veil
pokedex_entry: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.

name: Snover
pokedex_entry: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.

name: Abomasnow
pokedex_entry: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

name: Weavile
pokedex_entry: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

name: Magnezone
pokedex_entry: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it’s being controlled by some mysterious being.

name: Lickilicky
pokedex_entry: Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

name: Rhyperior
pokedex_entry: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

name: Tangrowth
pokedex_entry: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Electivire
pokedex_entry: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

name: Magmortar
pokedex_entry: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Togekiss
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly been seen at all.

name: Yanmega
pokedex_entry: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes’ heads instantly while flying by at high speed.

name: Leafeon
pokedex_entry: Galarians favor the distinctive aroma that drifts from this Pokémon’s leaves. There’s a popular perfume made using that scent.

name: Glaceon
pokedex_entry: Any who become captivated by the beauty of the snowfall that Glaceon creates will be frozen before they know it.

name: Gliscor
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Sand Veil, Poison Heal
pokedex_entry: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: Mamoswine
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

name: Porygon Z
pokedex_entry: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

name: Gallade
pokedex_entry: True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.

name: Probopass
pokedex_entry: It radiates such a powerful magnetic field that nearby electrical appliances become unusable.

name: Dusknoir
pokedex_entry: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.

name: Froslass
pokedex_entry: After a woman met her end on a snowy mountain, her regrets lingered on. From them, this Pokémon was born. Its favorite food is frozen souls.

name: Rotom
pokedex_entry: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

name: Uxie
pokedex_entry: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: Mesprit
pokedex_entry: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf
pokedex_entry: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Dialga
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

name: Palkia
pokedex_entry: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

name: Heatran
pokedex_entry: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Regigigas
pokedex_entry: All over the world, there are legends that tell of Regigigas creating other Pokémon in its own image.

name: Giratina Altered
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
pokedex_entry: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
pokedex_entry: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: Manaphy
pokedex_entry: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
pokedex_entry: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

name: Shaymin Land
pokedex_entry: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Arceus
pokedex_entry: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

name: Victini
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Snivy
pokedex_entry: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Servine
pokedex_entry: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: Serperior
pokedex_entry: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s noble eyes.

name: Tepig
pokedex_entry: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: Pignite
pokedex_entry: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.

name: Emboar
pokedex_entry: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: Oshawott
pokedex_entry: The scalchop on its stomach isn’t just used for battle--it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

name: Dewott
pokedex_entry: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: Samurott
pokedex_entry: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

name: Patrat
pokedex_entry: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: Watchog
pokedex_entry: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

name: Lillipup
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.

name: Herdier
pokedex_entry: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon. So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was the first Pokémon to partner with people.

name: Stoutland
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon seem to enjoy living with humans. Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up to people in about three days.

name: Purrloin
pokedex_entry: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.

name: Liepard
pokedex_entry: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

name: Pansage
pokedex_entry: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

name: Simisage
pokedex_entry: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.

name: Pansear
pokedex_entry: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

name: Simisear
pokedex_entry: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

name: Panpour
pokedex_entry: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

name: Simipour
pokedex_entry: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

name: Munna
pokedex_entry: Late at night, it appears beside people’s pillows. As it feeds on dreams, the patterns on its body give off a faint glow.

name: Musharna
pokedex_entry: When dark mists emanate from its body, don’t get too near. If you do, your nightmares will become reality.

name: Pidove
pokedex_entry: Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you’re scattering food for them, be careful— several hundred of them can gather at once.

name: Tranquill
pokedex_entry: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.

name: Unfezant
pokedex_entry: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.

name: Blitzle
abilities: Lightning Rod, Motor Drive, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: Zebstrika
abilities: Lightning Rod, Motor Drive, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: Roggenrola
pokedex_entry: It’s as hard as steel, but apparently a long soak in water will cause it to soften a bit.

name: Boldore
pokedex_entry: If you see its orange crystals start to glow, be wary. It’s about to fire off bursts of energy.

name: Gigalith
pokedex_entry: This hardy Pokémon can often be found on construction sites and in mines, working alongside people and Copperajah.

name: Woobat
pokedex_entry: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s evidence that Woobat live there.

name: Swoobat
pokedex_entry: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a little while.

name: Drilbur
abilities: Sand Rush, Sand Force, Mold Breaker
pokedex_entry: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

name: Excadrill
abilities: Sand Rush, Sand Force, Mold Breaker
pokedex_entry: It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

name: Audino
pokedex_entry: Audino’s sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino’s ears.

name: Timburr
pokedex_entry: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

name: Gurdurr
pokedex_entry: It shows off its muscles to Machoke and other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the other Pokémon, it lies low for a little while.

name: Conkeldurr
pokedex_entry: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete, even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

name: Tympole
pokedex_entry: Graceful ripples running across the water’s surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.

name: Palpitoad
pokedex_entry: It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.

name: Seismitoad
abilities: Swift Swim, Poison Touch, Water Absorb
pokedex_entry: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.

name: Throh
pokedex_entry: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh’s belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer’s sweat.

name: Sawk
pokedex_entry: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it’s best to quietly pass by.

name: Sewaddle
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

name: Swadloon
pokedex_entry: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny
pokedex_entry: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

name: Venipede
pokedex_entry: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

name: Whirlipede
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

name: Scolipede
pokedex_entry: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

name: Cottonee
pokedex_entry: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

name: Whimsicott
pokedex_entry: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it’ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

name: Petilil
pokedex_entry: Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pokémon’s head results in a liquid that’s sometimes used as a bug repellent.

name: Lilligant
pokedex_entry: It’s believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant’s head to bloom.

name: Basculin Red Striped
