pokedex_entry: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch— many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: Sandile
pokedex_entry: The desert gets cold at night, so when the sun sets, this Pokémon burrows deep into the sand and sleeps until sunrise.

name: Krokorok
pokedex_entry: Krokorok has specialized eyes that enable it to see in the dark. This ability lets Krokorok hunt in the dead of night without getting lost.

name: Krookodile
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sands. Krookodile’s mighty jaws can bite through heavy plates of iron with almost no effort at all.

name: Darumaka
pokedex_entry: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

name: Darmanitan Standard
pokedex_entry: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

name: Maractus
pokedex_entry: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

name: Dwebble
pokedex_entry: When it finds a stone appealing, it creates a hole inside it and uses it as its home. This Pokémon is the natural enemy of Roggenrola and Rolycoly.

name: Crustle
pokedex_entry: This highly territorial Pokémon prefers dry climates. It won’t come out of its boulder on rainy days.

name: Scraggy
pokedex_entry: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.

name: Scrafty
pokedex_entry: As halfhearted as this Pokémon’s kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr’s concrete pillars.

name: Sigilyph
abilities: Wonder Skin, Magic Guard, Tinted Lens
pokedex_entry: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians’ emissaries.

name: Yamask
pokedex_entry: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that’s said to have been the face it had when it was still human.

name: Cofagrigus
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.

name: Tirtouga
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

name: Carracosta
pokedex_entry: Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta’s own shell grows thick and sturdy.

name: Archen
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it’s very good at jumping.

name: Archeops
pokedex_entry: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.

name: Trubbish
pokedex_entry: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.

name: Garbodor
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

name: Zorua
pokedex_entry: Zorua is a timid Pokémon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua’s ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

name: Zoroark
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.

name: Minccino
pokedex_entry: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

name: Cinccino
pokedex_entry: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

name: Gothita
pokedex_entry: Though they’re still only babies, there’s psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.

name: Gothorita
pokedex_entry: It’s said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.

name: Gothitelle
pokedex_entry: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It’s also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.

name: Solosis
pokedex_entry: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

name: Duosion
pokedex_entry: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.

name: Reuniclus
pokedex_entry: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

name: Ducklett
pokedex_entry: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

name: Swanna
pokedex_entry: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

name: Vanillite
abilities: Ice Body, Snow Cloak, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

name: Vanillish
abilities: Ice Body, Snow Cloak, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.

name: Vanilluxe
abilities: Ice Body, Snow Warning, Weak Armor
pokedex_entry: When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.

name: Deerling
pokedex_entry: Their coloring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.

name: Sawsbuck
pokedex_entry: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

name: Emolga
pokedex_entry: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.

name: Karrablast
pokedex_entry: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

name: Escavalier
pokedex_entry: They use shells they’ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They’re very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.

name: Foongus
pokedex_entry: No one knows what the Poké Ball–like pattern on Foongus means or why Foongus has it.

name: Amoonguss
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren’t washed off quickly, they’ll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.

name: Frillish
pokedex_entry: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean’s surface.

name: Jellicent
pokedex_entry: Most of this Pokémon’s body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.

name: Alomomola
pokedex_entry: It uses its special mucus to close the wounds of injured Pokémon. The reason for this behavior remains unknown.

name: Joltik
pokedex_entry: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t produce a charge on its own.

name: Galvantula
pokedex_entry: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

name: Ferroseed
pokedex_entry: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn’t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.

name: Ferrothorn
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

name: Klink
pokedex_entry: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

name: Klang
pokedex_entry: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

name: Klinklang
pokedex_entry: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

name: Tynamo
pokedex_entry: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
pokedex_entry: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

name: Eelektross
pokedex_entry: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

name: Elgyem
pokedex_entry: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: Beheeyem
pokedex_entry: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

name: Litwick
pokedex_entry: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

name: Lampent
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it’s feared as an emissary of death.

name: Chandelure
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

name: Axew
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other’s strength.

name: Fraxure
pokedex_entry: After battle, this Pokémon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusks—if one breaks, it will never grow back.

name: Haxorus
pokedex_entry: Its resilient tusks are its pride and joy. It licks up dirt to take in the minerals it needs to keep its tusks in top condition.

name: Cubchoo
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn’t like.

name: Beartic
abilities: Snow Cloak, Slush Rush, Swift Swim
pokedex_entry: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.

name: Cryogonal
pokedex_entry: With its icy chains, Cryogonal freezes those it encounters. It then takes its victims away to somewhere unknown.

name: Shelmet
pokedex_entry: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

name: Accelgor
pokedex_entry: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

name: Stunfisk
pokedex_entry: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokémon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.

name: Mienfoo
pokedex_entry: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

name: Mienshao
pokedex_entry: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

name: Druddigon
abilities: Rough Skin, Sheer Force, Mold Breaker
pokedex_entry: Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body gets too cold.

name: Golett
pokedex_entry: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

name: Golurk
pokedex_entry: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

name: Pawniard
pokedex_entry: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

name: Bisharp
pokedex_entry: It’s accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

name: Bouffalant
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

name: Rufflet
pokedex_entry: If it spies a strong Pokémon, Rufflet can’t resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses, it starts bawling.

name: Braviary
pokedex_entry: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokémon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.

name: Vullaby
pokedex_entry: It wears a bone to protect its rear. It often squabbles with others of its kind over particularly comfy bones.

name: Mandibuzz
pokedex_entry: Although it’s a bit of a ruffian, this Pokémon will take lost Vullaby under its wing and care for them till they’re ready to leave the nest.

name: Heatmor
pokedex_entry: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

name: Durant
pokedex_entry: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.

name: Deino
pokedex_entry: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.

name: Zweilous
pokedex_entry: While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.

name: Hydreigon
pokedex_entry: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.

name: Larvesta
pokedex_entry: The people of ancient times believed that Larvesta fell from the sun.

name: Volcarona
pokedex_entry: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it’s trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.

name: Cobalion
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion, fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region’s Pokémon.

name: Terrakion
pokedex_entry: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokémon.

name: Virizion
pokedex_entry: A legend tells of this Pokémon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokémon of the Unova region.

name: Tornadus Incarnate
pokedex_entry: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: Thundurus Incarnate
pokedex_entry: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Reshiram
pokedex_entry: Flames spew from its tail as it flies through the sky like a jet airplane. It’s said that this Pokémon will scorch the world.

name: Zekrom
pokedex_entry: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.

name: Landorus Incarnate
pokedex_entry: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

name: Kyurem
pokedex_entry: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.

name: Keldeo Ordinary
pokedex_entry: Cobalion, Terrakion, and Virizion taught this Pokémon how to fight. It dashes across the world, seeking more opportunities to further its training.

name: Meloetta Aria
pokedex_entry: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: Genesect
pokedex_entry: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

name: Chespin
pokedex_entry: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: Quilladin
pokedex_entry: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

name: Chesnaught
pokedex_entry: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

name: Fennekin
pokedex_entry: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Braixen
pokedex_entry: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

name: Delphox
pokedex_entry: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

name: Froakie
pokedex_entry: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: Frogadier
pokedex_entry: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja
pokedex_entry: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

name: Bunnelby
pokedex_entry: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.

name: Diggersby
pokedex_entry: With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It’s a huge help during tunnel construction.

name: Fletchling
pokedex_entry: Its melodious cries are actually warnings. Fletchling will mercilessly peck at anything that enters its territory.

name: Fletchinder
pokedex_entry: Fletchinder launches embers into the den of its prey. When the prey comes leaping out, Fletchinder’s sharp talons finish it off.

name: Talonflame
pokedex_entry: Talonflame mainly preys upon other bird Pokémon. To intimidate opponents, it sends embers spewing from gaps between its feathers.

name: Scatterbug
abilities: Shield Dust, Compound Eyes, Friend Guard
pokedex_entry: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

name: Spewpa
pokedex_entry: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

name: Vivillon
abilities: Shield Dust, Compound Eyes, Friend Guard
pokedex_entry: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

name: Litleo
pokedex_entry: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

name: Pyroar
pokedex_entry: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

name: Flabebe
pokedex_entry: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

name: Floette
pokedex_entry: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

name: Florges
pokedex_entry: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

name: Skiddo
pokedex_entry: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: Gogoat
pokedex_entry: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

name: Pancham
pokedex_entry: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master’s actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

name: Pangoro
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.

name: Furfrou
pokedex_entry: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

name: Espurr
pokedex_entry: Though Espurr’s expression never changes, behind that blank stare is an intense struggle to contain its devastating psychic power.

name: Meowstic Male
pokedex_entry: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

name: Honedge
pokedex_entry: Honedge’s soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge’s body.

name: Doublade
pokedex_entry: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.

name: Aegislash Shield
pokedex_entry: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.

name: Spritzee
pokedex_entry: A scent pouch within this Pokémon’s body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

name: Aromatisse
pokedex_entry: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon’s companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

name: Swirlix
pokedex_entry: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

name: Slurpuff
pokedex_entry: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

name: Inkay
pokedex_entry: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

name: Malamar
pokedex_entry: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar’s control.

name: Binacle
pokedex_entry: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

name: Barbaracle
pokedex_entry: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

name: Skrelp
pokedex_entry: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

name: Dragalge
pokedex_entry: Dragalge uses a poisonous liquid capable of corroding metal to send tankers that enter its territory to the bottom of the sea.

name: Clauncher
pokedex_entry: Clauncher’s claws can fall off during battle, but they’ll regenerate. The meat inside the claws is popular as a delicacy in Galar.

name: Clawitzer
pokedex_entry: After using the feelers on its oversized claw to detect the location of prey, Clawitzer launches a cannonball of water at its target.

name: Helioptile
abilities: Dry Skin, Sand Veil, Solar Power
pokedex_entry: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.

name: Heliolisk
abilities: Dry Skin, Sand Veil, Solar Power
pokedex_entry: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

name: Tyrunt
pokedex_entry: This is an ancient Pokémon, revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition, and it’ll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.

name: Tyrantrum
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.

name: Amaura
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

name: Aurorus
pokedex_entry: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It’s said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.

name: Sylveon
pokedex_entry: By releasing enmity-erasing waves from its ribbonlike feelers, Sylveon stops any conflict.

name: Hawlucha
pokedex_entry: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.

name: Dedenne
pokedex_entry: A Dedenne’s whiskers pick up electrical waves other Dedenne send out. These Pokémon share locations of food or electricity with one another.

name: Carbink
pokedex_entry: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.

name: Goomy
pokedex_entry: Because most of its body is water, it will dry up if the weather becomes too arid. It’s considered the weakest dragon Pokémon.

name: Sliggoo
pokedex_entry: Although this Pokémon isn’t very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

name: Goodra
pokedex_entry: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don’t mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.

name: Klefki
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is constantly collecting keys. Entrust a Klefki with important keys, and the Pokémon will protect them no matter what.

name: Phantump
pokedex_entry: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

name: Trevenant
pokedex_entry: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

name: Pumpkaboo Average
pokedex_entry: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

name: Gourgeist Average
pokedex_entry: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

name: Bergmite
pokedex_entry: They chill the air around them to −150 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.

name: Avalugg
pokedex_entry: At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

name: Noibat
pokedex_entry: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.

name: Noivern
pokedex_entry: Aggressive and cruel, this Pokémon will ruthlessly torment enemies that are helpless in the dark.

name: Xerneas
pokedex_entry: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

name: Yveltal
pokedex_entry: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

name: Zygarde 50
pokedex_entry: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

name: Diancie
pokedex_entry: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: Hoopa
pokedex_entry: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

name: Volcanion
pokedex_entry: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

name: Rowlet
pokedex_entry: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.

name: Dartrix
pokedex_entry: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

name: Decidueye
pokedex_entry: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye’s shots never miss.

name: Litten
pokedex_entry: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.

name: Torracat
pokedex_entry: In the midst of battle, the fire pouch on Torracat’s neck rings like a bell and produces stronger flames than usual.

name: Incineroar
pokedex_entry: It excels at violent, no-holds-barred battles. The temperature of the flames that issue from its navel exceeds 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Popplio
pokedex_entry: It creates special bouncy balloons to send at its opponents. When the balloons pop, the sheer force of their bursting is what deals damage.

name: Brionne
pokedex_entry: As if dancing, it artfully dodges the attacks of its enemies. All the while, it’s busy forming a bunch of balloons to overwhelm its foes.

name: Primarina
pokedex_entry: With its mouth, it makes sonic waves that sound like beautiful singing. It uses the sonic waves to control its water balloons.

name: Pikipek
pokedex_entry: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

name: Trumbeak
pokedex_entry: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

name: Toucannon
abilities: Keen Eye, Skill Link, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

name: Yungoos
pokedex_entry: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

name: Gumshoos
pokedex_entry: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

name: Grubbin
pokedex_entry: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

name: Charjabug
pokedex_entry: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
pokedex_entry: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

name: Crabrawler
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Iron Fist, Anger Point
pokedex_entry: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

name: Crabominable
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Iron Fist, Anger Point
pokedex_entry: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

name: Oricorio Baile
pokedex_entry: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: Cutiefly
abilities: Honey Gather, Shield Dust, Sweet Veil
pokedex_entry: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur’s pollen.

name: Ribombee
abilities: Honey Gather, Shield Dust, Sweet Veil
pokedex_entry: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs’ effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

name: Rockruff
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

name: Lycanroc Midday
pokedex_entry: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.

name: Wishiwashi Solo
pokedex_entry: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

name: Mareanie
pokedex_entry: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it’s impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

name: Toxapex
pokedex_entry: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.

name: Mudbray
pokedex_entry: Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It’s skilled at making use of mud.

name: Mudsdale
pokedex_entry: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale’s legs sets harder than stone. It’s so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.

name: Dewpider
pokedex_entry: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

name: Araquanid
pokedex_entry: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

name: Fomantis
pokedex_entry: When bathed in sunlight, this Pokémon emits a pleasantly sweet scent, which causes bug Pokémon to gather around it.

name: Lurantis
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.

name: Morelull
pokedex_entry: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

name: Shiinotic
pokedex_entry: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: Salandit
pokedex_entry: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit’s poisonous gas.

name: Salazzle
pokedex_entry: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.

name: Stufful
pokedex_entry: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

name: Bewear
pokedex_entry: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

name: Bounsweet
pokedex_entry: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokémon.

name: Steenee
pokedex_entry: As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.

name: Tsareena
abilities: Leaf Guard, Queenly Majesty, Sweet Veil
pokedex_entry: This feared Pokémon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.

name: Comfey
pokedex_entry: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won’t wither once they’re attached to a Comfey.

name: Oranguru
pokedex_entry: With waves of its fan—made from leaves and its own fur—Oranguru skillfully gives instructions to other Pokémon.

name: Passimian
pokedex_entry: Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.

name: Wimpod
pokedex_entry: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

name: Golisopod
pokedex_entry: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

name: Sandygast
pokedex_entry: Grudges of the dead have possessed a mound of sand and become a Pokémon. Sandygast is fond of the shovel on its head.

name: Palossand
pokedex_entry: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.

name: Pyukumuku
pokedex_entry: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

name: Type Null
pokedex_entry: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

name: Silvally
pokedex_entry: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

name: Minior Red Meteor
pokedex_entry: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.

name: Komala
pokedex_entry: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

name: Turtonator
pokedex_entry: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

name: Togedemaru
pokedex_entry: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Mimikyu Disguised
pokedex_entry: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

name: Bruxish
pokedex_entry: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

name: Drampa
pokedex_entry: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

name: Dhelmise
pokedex_entry: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

name: Jangmo O
pokedex_entry: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

name: Hakamo O
pokedex_entry: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.

name: Kommo O
pokedex_entry: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

name: Tapu Koko
pokedex_entry: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

name: Tapu Lele
pokedex_entry: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

name: Tapu Bulu
pokedex_entry: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

name: Tapu Fini
pokedex_entry: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

name: Cosmog
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon came from another universe. Its gaseous body is so light that even a gentle breeze can blow it away.

name: Cosmoem
pokedex_entry: The absorption of starlight fuels this Pokémon’s growth. The shell that encases it is harder than any known material.

name: Solgaleo
pokedex_entry: When light radiates from its body, this Pokémon could almost appear to be the sun. It will dispel any darkness and light up the world.

name: Lunala
pokedex_entry: Known as the Beast That Calls the Moon, this Pokémon lives by taking in any and all light and converting it into its own energy.

name: Nihilego
pokedex_entry: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.

name: Buzzwole
pokedex_entry: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

name: Pheromosa
pokedex_entry: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.

name: Xurkitree
pokedex_entry: One of the mysterious life-forms known as Ultra Beasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanate from its entire body, according to witnesses.

name: Celesteela
pokedex_entry: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnesses observed it flying across the sky at high speed.

name: Kartana
pokedex_entry: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

name: Guzzlord
pokedex_entry: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed whole buildings, according to reports. It’s one of the Ultra Beasts.

name: Necrozma
pokedex_entry: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.

name: Magearna
pokedex_entry: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

name: Marshadow
pokedex_entry: By slipping into the shadow of a martial arts master and copying their movements, this Pokémon learned the ultimate techniques.

name: Poipole
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Naganadel
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Stakataka
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Blacephalon
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Zeraora
pokedex_entry: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.

name: Meltan
pokedex_entry: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Melmetal
pokedex_entry: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: Grookey
pokedex_entry: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: Thwackey
pokedex_entry: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

name: Rillaboom
pokedex_entry: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: Scorbunny
pokedex_entry: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

name: Raboot
pokedex_entry: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

name: Cinderace
pokedex_entry: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

name: Sobble
pokedex_entry: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

name: Drizzile
pokedex_entry: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

name: Inteleon
pokedex_entry: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: Skwovet
pokedex_entry: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

name: Greedent
pokedex_entry: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn’t notice the loss.

name: Rookidee
pokedex_entry: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

name: Corvisquire
pokedex_entry: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

name: Corviknight
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

name: Blipbug
pokedex_entry: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

name: Dottler
pokedex_entry: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

name: Orbeetle
pokedex_entry: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

name: Nickit
pokedex_entry: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

name: Thievul
pokedex_entry: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

name: Gossifleur
pokedex_entry: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

name: Eldegoss
pokedex_entry: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: Wooloo
pokedex_entry: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: Dubwool
pokedex_entry: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: Chewtle
abilities: Strong Jaw, Shell Armor, Swift Swim
pokedex_entry: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

name: Drednaw
abilities: Strong Jaw, Shell Armor, Swift Swim
pokedex_entry: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: Yamper
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

name: Boltund
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

name: Rolycoly
pokedex_entry: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: Carkol
abilities: Steam Engine, Flame Body, Flash Fire
pokedex_entry: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

name: Coalossal
abilities: Steam Engine, Flame Body, Flash Fire
pokedex_entry: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Applin
pokedex_entry: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.

name: Flapple
pokedex_entry: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

name: Appletun
pokedex_entry: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

name: Silicobra
abilities: Sand Spit, Shed Skin, Sand Veil
pokedex_entry: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

name: Sandaconda
abilities: Sand Spit, Shed Skin, Sand Veil
pokedex_entry: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

name: Cramorant
pokedex_entry: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

name: Arrokuda
pokedex_entry: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.

name: Barraskewda
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

name: Toxel
pokedex_entry: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

name: Toxtricity Amped
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a guitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

name: Sizzlipede
abilities: Flash Fire, White Smoke, Flame Body
pokedex_entry: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
abilities: Flash Fire, White Smoke, Flame Body
pokedex_entry: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: Clobbopus
pokedex_entry: It’s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Grapploct
pokedex_entry: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

name: Sinistea
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

name: Polteageist
pokedex_entry: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

name: Hatenna
pokedex_entry: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures’ emotions. If you don’t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

name: Hattrem
pokedex_entry: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

name: Hatterene
pokedex_entry: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

name: Impidimp
pokedex_entry: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

name: Morgrem
pokedex_entry: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it’s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

name: Grimmsnarl
pokedex_entry: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: Obstagoon
pokedex_entry: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

name: Perrserker
abilities: Battle Armor, Tough Claws, Steely Spirit
pokedex_entry: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

name: Cursola
pokedex_entry: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.

name: Sirfetchd
pokedex_entry: Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s leek withers, it will retire from combat.

name: Mr Rime
abilities: Tangled Feet, Screen Cleaner, Ice Body
pokedex_entry: It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

name: Runerigus
pokedex_entry: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

name: Milcery
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

name: Alcremie
pokedex_entry: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it’s decorated with cream.

name: Falinks
pokedex_entry: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass’s orders are absolute.

name: Pincurchin
pokedex_entry: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

name: Snom
pokedex_entry: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

name: Frosmoth
pokedex_entry: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Stonjourner
pokedex_entry: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

name: Eiscue Ice
pokedex_entry: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

name: Indeedee Male
pokedex_entry: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

name: Morpeko Full Belly
pokedex_entry: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.

name: Cufant
pokedex_entry: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It’s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: Copperajah
pokedex_entry: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

name: Dracozolt
pokedex_entry: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

name: Arctozolt
pokedex_entry: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

name: Dracovish
abilities: Water Absorb, Strong Jaw, Sand Rush
pokedex_entry: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

name: Arctovish
abilities: Water Absorb, Ice Body, Slush Rush
pokedex_entry: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

name: Duraludon
pokedex_entry: Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: Dreepy
pokedex_entry: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

name: Drakloak
pokedex_entry: It’s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: Dragapult
pokedex_entry: When it isn’t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

name: Zacian
pokedex_entry: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: Zamazenta
pokedex_entry: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: Eternatus
pokedex_entry: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

name: Kubfu
pokedex_entry: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

name: Urshifu Single Strike
pokedex_entry: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

name: Zarude
pokedex_entry: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It’s incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

name: Regieleki
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokémon’s latent power.

name: Regidrago
pokedex_entry: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

name: Glastrier
pokedex_entry: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It’s also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

name: Spectrier
pokedex_entry: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.

name: Calyrex
pokedex_entry: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

name: Wyrdeer
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Kleavor
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Ursaluna
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Basculegion Male
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Sneasler
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Overqwil
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Enamorus Incarnate
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Sprigatito
pokedex_entry: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

name: Floragato
pokedex_entry: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

name: Meowscarada
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

name: Fuecoco
pokedex_entry: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

name: Crocalor
pokedex_entry: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon’s head.

name: Skeledirge
pokedex_entry: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.

name: Quaxly
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime."

name: Quaxwell
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

name: Quaquaval
pokedex_entry: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

name: Lechonk
pokedex_entry: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Oinkologne Male
pokedex_entry: Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.

name: Tarountula
pokedex_entry: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon’s natural enemy.

name: Spidops
pokedex_entry: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

name: Nymble
pokedex_entry: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Lokix
pokedex_entry: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

name: Pawmi
pokedex_entry: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

name: Pawmo
abilities: Volt Absorb, Natural Cure, Iron Fist
pokedex_entry: When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

name: Pawmot
abilities: Volt Absorb, Natural Cure, Iron Fist
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

name: Tandemaus
pokedex_entry: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.

name: Maushold Family Of Four
pokedex_entry: The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokémon, but nobody knows for sure.

name: Fidough
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon’s vicinity.

name: Dachsbun
pokedex_entry: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon’s body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

name: Smoliv
pokedex_entry: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Dolliv
pokedex_entry: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

name: Arboliva
pokedex_entry: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

name: Squawkabilly Green Plumage
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Nacli
pokedex_entry: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

name: Naclstack
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey’s body.

name: Garganacl
pokedex_entry: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

name: Charcadet
pokedex_entry: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge
pokedex_entry: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

name: Ceruledge
pokedex_entry: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

name: Tadbulb
pokedex_entry: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

name: Bellibolt
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

name: Wattrel
pokedex_entry: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

name: Kilowattrel
pokedex_entry: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

name: Maschiff
pokedex_entry: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff’s face.

name: Mabosstiff
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can store energy in its large dewlap. Mabosstiff unleashes this energy all at once to blow away enemies.

name: Shroodle
pokedex_entry: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

name: Grafaiai
pokedex_entry: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

name: Bramblin
pokedex_entry: A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokémon.

name: Brambleghast
pokedex_entry: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.

name: Toedscool
pokedex_entry: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

name: Toedscruel
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

name: Klawf
pokedex_entry: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can’t remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

name: Capsakid
pokedex_entry: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.

name: Scovillain
pokedex_entry: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.

name: Rellor
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.

name: Rabsca
pokedex_entry: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.

name: Flittle
pokedex_entry: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon’s belly.

name: Espathra
pokedex_entry: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.

name: Tinkatink
pokedex_entry: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.

name: Tinkatuff
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

name: Tinkaton
pokedex_entry: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.

name: Wiglett
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

name: Wugtrio
pokedex_entry: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.

name: Bombirdier
abilities: Big Pecks, Keen Eye, Rocky Payload
pokedex_entry: It gathers things up in an apron made from shed feathers added to the Pokémon’s chest feathers, then drops those things from high places for fun.

name: Finizen
pokedex_entry: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

name: Palafin Zero
abilities: Zero To Hero, Zero To Hero
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

name: Varoom
pokedex_entry: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

name: Revavroom
pokedex_entry: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders—now numbering eight—to generate energy.

name: Cyclizar
pokedex_entry: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.

name: Orthworm
pokedex_entry: When attacked, this Pokémon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.

name: Glimmet
pokedex_entry: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

name: Glimmora
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon detects danger, it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.

name: Greavard
pokedex_entry: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

name: Houndstone
pokedex_entry: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.

name: Flamigo
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

name: Cetoddle
abilities: Thick Fat, Snow Cloak, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.

name: Cetitan
abilities: Thick Fat, Slush Rush, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon wanders around snowy, icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.

name: Veluza
pokedex_entry: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

name: Dondozo
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

name: Tatsugiri Curly
pokedex_entry: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

name: Annihilape
pokedex_entry: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

name: Clodsire
pokedex_entry: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.

name: Farigiraf
abilities: Cud Chew, Armor Tail, Sap Sipper
pokedex_entry: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokémon is 10 times stronger than Girafarig’s.

name: Dudunsparce Two Segment
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

name: Kingambit
pokedex_entry: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

name: Great Tusk
pokedex_entry: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

name: Scream Tail
pokedex_entry: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokémon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.

name: Brute Bonnet
pokedex_entry: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

name: Flutter Mane
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.

name: Slither Wing
pokedex_entry: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

name: Sandy Shocks
pokedex_entry: No records exist of this Pokémon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.

name: Iron Treads
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.

name: Iron Bundle
pokedex_entry: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.

name: Iron Hands
pokedex_entry: It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.

name: Iron Jugulis
pokedex_entry: It resembles a certain Pokémon introduced in a paranormal magazine, described as the offspring of a Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.

name: Iron Moth
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.

name: Iron Thorns
pokedex_entry: It has some similarities to a Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.

name: Frigibax
pokedex_entry: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.

name: Arctibax
pokedex_entry: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

name: Baxcalibur
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

name: Gimmighoul
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

name: Gholdengo
pokedex_entry: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

name: Wo Chien
pokedex_entry: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokémon.

name: Chien Pao
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.

name: Ting Lu
pokedex_entry: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokémon.

name: Chi Yu
pokedex_entry: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.

name: Roaring Moon
pokedex_entry: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.

name: Iron Valiant
pokedex_entry: It has some similarities to a mad scientist’s invention covered in a paranormal magazine.

name: Koraidon
pokedex_entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Miraidon
pokedex_entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

name: Walking Wake
pokedex_entry: This ferocious creature is shrouded in mystery. It's named after an aquatic monster mentioned in an old expedition journal.

name: Iron Leaves
pokedex_entry: Many of its physical characteristics match those of a Virizion from the future that was covered in a paranormal magazine.

name: Dipplin
pokedex_entry: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokémon. Its evolution was triggered by a special apple grown only in one place.

name: Poltchageist
pokedex_entry: Supposedly, the regrets of a tea ceremony master who died before perfecting his craft lingered in some matcha and became a Pokémon.

name: Sinistcha
pokedex_entry: It pretends to be tea, trying to fool people into drinking it so it can drain their life-force. Its ruse is generally unsuccessful.

name: Okidogi
pokedex_entry: After all its muscles were stimulated by the toxic chain around its neck, Okidogi transformed and gained a powerful physique.

name: Munkidori
pokedex_entry: The chain is made from toxins that enhance capabilities. It stimulated Munkidori's brain and caused the Pokémon's psychic powers to bloom.

name: Fezandipiti
pokedex_entry: Fezandipiti owes its beautiful looks and lovely voice to the toxic stimulants emanating from the chain wrapped around its body.

name: Ogerpon
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

name: Archaludon
pokedex_entry: It gathers static electricity from its surroundings. The beams it launches when down on all fours are tremendously powerful.

name: Hydrapple
pokedex_entry: Seven syrpents live inside an apple made of syrup. The syrpent in the center is the commander.

name: Gouging Fire
pokedex_entry: There are scant few reports of this creature being sighted. One short video shows it rampaging and spouting pillars of flame.

name: Raging Bolt
pokedex_entry: It's said to incinerate everything around it with lightning launched from its fur. Very little is known about this creature.

name: Iron Boulder
pokedex_entry: It resembles a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a Terrakion that had been modified by an evil organization.

name: Iron Crown
pokedex_entry: It resembles a mysterious object introduced in a paranormal magazine as a cutting-edge weapon shaped like a Cobalion.

name: Terapagos
pokedex_entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokémon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.

name: Pecharunt
pokedex_entry: It feeds others toxic mochi that draw out desires and capabilities. Those who eat the mochi fall under Pecharunt’s control, chained to its will.

name: Deoxys Attack
pokedex_entry: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Deoxys Defense
pokedex_entry: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Deoxys Speed
pokedex_entry: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Wormadam Sandy
pokedex_entry: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Wormadam Trash
pokedex_entry: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Shaymin Sky
pokedex_entry: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Giratina Origin
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Rotom Heat
pokedex_entry: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

name: Rotom Wash
pokedex_entry: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

name: Rotom Frost
pokedex_entry: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

name: Rotom Fan
pokedex_entry: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

name: Rotom Mow
pokedex_entry: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

name: Castform Sunny
pokedex_entry: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

name: Castform Rainy
pokedex_entry: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

name: Castform Snowy
pokedex_entry: It changes its form depending on the weather. Changes in the temperature or humidity appear to affect its cellular structure.

name: Basculin Blue Striped
pokedex_entry: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch— many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: Darmanitan Zen
pokedex_entry: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

name: Meloetta Pirouette
pokedex_entry: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: Tornadus Therian
pokedex_entry: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: Thundurus Therian
pokedex_entry: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Landorus Therian
pokedex_entry: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

name: Kyurem Black
pokedex_entry: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.

name: Kyurem White
pokedex_entry: Dwelling within it is a power even greater than that of Reshiram or Zekrom, but the extreme cold keeps that power bound.

name: Keldeo Resolute
pokedex_entry: Cobalion, Terrakion, and Virizion taught this Pokémon how to fight. It dashes across the world, seeking more opportunities to further its training.

name: Meowstic Female
pokedex_entry: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

name: Aegislash Blade
pokedex_entry: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.

name: Pumpkaboo Small
pokedex_entry: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

name: Pumpkaboo Large
pokedex_entry: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

name: Pumpkaboo Super
pokedex_entry: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

name: Gourgeist Small
