pokedex_entry: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

name: Gourgeist Large
pokedex_entry: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

name: Gourgeist Super
pokedex_entry: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

name: Venusaur Mega
pokedex_entry: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Charizard Mega X
pokedex_entry: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

name: Charizard Mega Y
pokedex_entry: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

name: Blastoise Mega
pokedex_entry: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Alakazam Mega
pokedex_entry: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

name: Gengar Mega
pokedex_entry: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar’s doing.

name: Kangaskhan Mega
pokedex_entry: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

name: Pinsir Mega
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

name: Gyarados Mega
pokedex_entry: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

name: Aerodactyl Mega
pokedex_entry: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

name: Mewtwo Mega X
pokedex_entry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

name: Mewtwo Mega Y
pokedex_entry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

name: Ampharos Mega
pokedex_entry: The tail’s tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Scizor Mega
pokedex_entry: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor’s body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

name: Heracross Mega
pokedex_entry: Heracross loves sweet sap and will go looking through forests for it. The Pokémon uses its two antennae to pick up scents as it searches.

name: Houndoom Mega
pokedex_entry: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

name: Tyranitar Mega
pokedex_entry: Its body can’t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

name: Blaziken Mega
pokedex_entry: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

name: Gardevoir Mega
pokedex_entry: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.

name: Mawile Mega
pokedex_entry: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

name: Aggron Mega
pokedex_entry: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

name: Medicham Mega
pokedex_entry: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

name: Manectric Mega
pokedex_entry: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.

name: Banette Mega
pokedex_entry: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.

name: Absol Mega
pokedex_entry: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Garchomp Mega
pokedex_entry: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.

name: Lucario Mega
pokedex_entry: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.

name: Abomasnow Mega
pokedex_entry: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

name: Floette Eternal
pokedex_entry: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

name: Latias Mega
pokedex_entry: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Latios Mega
pokedex_entry: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

name: Swampert Mega
pokedex_entry: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break a boulder into pieces.

name: Sceptile Mega
pokedex_entry: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

name: Sableye Mega
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it’s believed that Sableye will steal people’s spirits away.

name: Altaria Mega
pokedex_entry: As it flies in a calm and relaxed manner, Altaria performs a humming song that would enrapture any audience.

name: Gallade Mega
pokedex_entry: True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.

name: Audino Mega
pokedex_entry: Audino’s sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino’s ears.

name: Sharpedo Mega
pokedex_entry: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

name: Slowbro Mega
pokedex_entry: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

name: Steelix Mega
pokedex_entry: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

name: Pidgeot Mega
pokedex_entry: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

name: Glalie Mega
pokedex_entry: It has a body of ice that won’t melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.

name: Diancie Mega
pokedex_entry: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: Metagross Mega
pokedex_entry: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

name: Kyogre Primal
pokedex_entry: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.

name: Groudon Primal
pokedex_entry: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with Kyogre.

name: Rayquaza Mega
pokedex_entry: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: Pikachu Rock Star
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Belle
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Pop Star
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Phd
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Libre
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Cosplay
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Hoopa Unbound
pokedex_entry: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

name: Camerupt Mega
pokedex_entry: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.

name: Lopunny Mega
pokedex_entry: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

name: Salamence Mega
pokedex_entry: Salamence is an unusual Pokémon in that it was able to evolve a body with wings just by constantly wishing to be able to fly.

name: Beedrill Mega
pokedex_entry: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

name: Rattata Alola
pokedex_entry: Its incisors continue growing until its death. If its Trainer doesn’t offer it a file to gnaw on, it will gnaw on door frames, table legs, and so on.

name: Raticate Alola
pokedex_entry: Its hind feet are webbed, so it’s a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.

name: Raticate Totem Alola
pokedex_entry: Its hind feet are webbed, so it’s a strong swimmer. It can cross rivers and sometimes even oceans.

name: Pikachu Original Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Hoenn Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Sinnoh Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Unova Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Kalos Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Pikachu Alola Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Raichu Alola
pokedex_entry: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

name: Sandshrew Alola
pokedex_entry: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

name: Sandslash Alola
pokedex_entry: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon’s spikes will feel when touched.

name: Vulpix Alola
pokedex_entry: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales Alola
pokedex_entry: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

name: Diglett Alola
abilities: Sand Veil, Tangling Hair, Sand Force
pokedex_entry: If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

name: Dugtrio Alola
abilities: Sand Veil, Tangling Hair, Sand Force
pokedex_entry: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

name: Meowth Alola
pokedex_entry: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

name: Persian Alola
pokedex_entry: Getting this prideful Pokémon to warm up to you takes a lot of effort, and it will claw at you the moment it gets annoyed.

name: Geodude Alola
pokedex_entry: Its round body makes it easy to pick up, but it is hard and heavy. It’s dangerous to play with them as if they were snowballs.

name: Graveler Alola
pokedex_entry: Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly.

name: Golem Alola
pokedex_entry: Its body can survive dynamite blasts without a single scratch, but it hates rain and humidity.

name: Grimer Alola
abilities: Poison Touch, Gluttony, Power Of Alchemy
pokedex_entry: Its main source of food is the slimy industrial waste of factories. This Pokémon’s numbers have been decreasing in recent years.

name: Muk Alola
abilities: Poison Touch, Gluttony, Power Of Alchemy
pokedex_entry: The stench it gives off will make your nose scrunch up. Still, there are Muk fans who think that’s a good thing.

name: Exeggutor Alola
pokedex_entry: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

name: Marowak Alola
abilities: Cursed Body, Lightning Rod, Rock Head
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

name: Greninja Battle Bond
pokedex_entry: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

name: Greninja Ash
pokedex_entry: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

name: Zygarde 10 Power Construct
pokedex_entry: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

name: Zygarde 50 Power Construct
pokedex_entry: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

name: Zygarde Complete
pokedex_entry: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

name: Gumshoos Totem
pokedex_entry: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but it’s always snoozing by nightfall.

name: Vikavolt Totem
pokedex_entry: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

name: Oricorio Pom Pom
pokedex_entry: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: Oricorio Pau
pokedex_entry: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: Oricorio Sensu
pokedex_entry: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: Lycanroc Midnight
abilities: Keen Eye, Vital Spirit, No Guard
pokedex_entry: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.

name: Wishiwashi School
pokedex_entry: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

name: Lurantis Totem
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.

name: Salazzle Totem
pokedex_entry: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.

name: Minior Orange Meteor
pokedex_entry: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.

name: Minior Yellow Meteor

name: Minior Violet

name: Mimikyu Busted
pokedex_entry: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

name: Mimikyu Totem Disguised
pokedex_entry: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

name: Mimikyu Totem Busted
pokedex_entry: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

name: Kommo O Totem
pokedex_entry: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

name: Magearna Original
pokedex_entry: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than 500 years ago, can understand human speech but cannot itself speak.

name: Pikachu Partner Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Marowak Totem
abilities: Cursed Body, Lightning Rod, Rock Head
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

name: Ribombee Totem
abilities: Honey Gather, Shield Dust, Sweet Veil
pokedex_entry: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs’ effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

name: Rockruff Own Tempo
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

name: Lycanroc Dusk
pokedex_entry: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.

name: Araquanid Totem
pokedex_entry: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

name: Togedemaru Totem
pokedex_entry: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Necrozma Dusk
pokedex_entry: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.

name: Necrozma Dawn
pokedex_entry: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.

name: Necrozma Ultra
pokedex_entry: It survives by absorbing light. After a long time spent slumbering underground, impurities accumulated within it, causing its body to darken.

name: Pikachu Starter
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Eevee Starter
pokedex_entry: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

name: Pikachu World Cap
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Meowth Galar
pokedex_entry: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

name: Ponyta Galar
pokedex_entry: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

name: Rapidash Galar
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Slowpoke Galar
pokedex_entry: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won’t feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won’t notice when its tail grows back, either.

name: Slowbro Galar
pokedex_entry: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

name: Farfetchd Galar
pokedex_entry: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

name: Weezing Galar
pokedex_entry: It mixes gases between its two bodies. It’s said that these Pokémon were seen all over the Galar region back in the day.

name: Mr Mime Galar
abilities: Vital Spirit, Screen Cleaner, Ice Body
pokedex_entry: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Articuno Galar
pokedex_entry: It’s said that this Pokémon’s beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

name: Zapdos Galar
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

name: Moltres Galar
pokedex_entry: It’s one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

name: Slowking Galar
pokedex_entry: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke’s latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

name: Corsola Galar
pokedex_entry: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

name: Zigzagoon Galar
pokedex_entry: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

name: Linoone Galar
pokedex_entry: Its fur is strong and supple. Shaving brushes made with shed Linoone hairs are highly prized.

name: Darumaka Galar
pokedex_entry: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

name: Darmanitan Galar Standard
pokedex_entry: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

name: Darmanitan Galar Zen
pokedex_entry: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

name: Yamask Galar
pokedex_entry: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that’s said to have been the face it had when it was still human.

name: Stunfisk Galar
pokedex_entry: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokémon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.

name: Zygarde 10
pokedex_entry: This is Zygarde’s form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

name: Cramorant Gulping
pokedex_entry: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

name: Cramorant Gorging
pokedex_entry: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

name: Toxtricity Low Key
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a guitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

name: Eiscue Noice
pokedex_entry: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

name: Indeedee Female
pokedex_entry: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

name: Morpeko Hangry
pokedex_entry: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.

name: Zacian Crowned
pokedex_entry: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: Zamazenta Crowned
pokedex_entry: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: Eternatus Eternamax
pokedex_entry: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

name: Urshifu Rapid Strike
pokedex_entry: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

name: Zarude Dada
pokedex_entry: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It’s incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

name: Calyrex Ice
pokedex_entry: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

name: Calyrex Shadow
pokedex_entry: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

name: Venusaur Gmax
pokedex_entry: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

name: Charizard Gmax
pokedex_entry: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

name: Blastoise Gmax
pokedex_entry: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

name: Butterfree Gmax
pokedex_entry: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

name: Pikachu Gmax
pokedex_entry: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Meowth Gmax
pokedex_entry: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

name: Machamp Gmax
pokedex_entry: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Gengar Gmax
pokedex_entry: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar’s doing.

name: Kingler Gmax
abilities: Hyper Cutter, Shell Armor, Sheer Force
pokedex_entry: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

name: Lapras Gmax
pokedex_entry: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Eevee Gmax
pokedex_entry: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

name: Snorlax Gmax
pokedex_entry: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Garbodor Gmax
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

name: Melmetal Gmax
pokedex_entry: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

name: Rillaboom Gmax
pokedex_entry: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: Cinderace Gmax
pokedex_entry: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

name: Inteleon Gmax
pokedex_entry: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: Corviknight Gmax
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

name: Orbeetle Gmax
pokedex_entry: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

name: Drednaw Gmax
abilities: Strong Jaw, Shell Armor, Swift Swim
pokedex_entry: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: Coalossal Gmax
abilities: Steam Engine, Flame Body, Flash Fire
pokedex_entry: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Flapple Gmax
pokedex_entry: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

name: Appletun Gmax
pokedex_entry: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

name: Sandaconda Gmax
abilities: Sand Spit, Shed Skin, Sand Veil
pokedex_entry: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

name: Toxtricity Amped Gmax
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a guitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

name: Centiskorch Gmax
abilities: Flash Fire, White Smoke, Flame Body
pokedex_entry: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: Hatterene Gmax
pokedex_entry: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

name: Grimmsnarl Gmax
pokedex_entry: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: Alcremie Gmax
pokedex_entry: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it’s decorated with cream.

name: Copperajah Gmax
pokedex_entry: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

name: Duraludon Gmax
pokedex_entry: Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: Urshifu Single Strike Gmax
pokedex_entry: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

name: Urshifu Rapid Strike Gmax
pokedex_entry: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

name: Toxtricity Low Key Gmax
pokedex_entry: When this Pokémon sounds as if it’s strumming a guitar, it’s actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

name: Growlithe Hisui
pokedex_entry: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine Hisui
pokedex_entry: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

name: Voltorb Hisui
pokedex_entry: It was discovered when Poké Balls were introduced. It is said that there is some connection.

name: Electrode Hisui
pokedex_entry: It explodes in response to even minor stimuli. It is feared, with the nickname of “The Bomb Ball.”

name: Typhlosion Hisui
pokedex_entry: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

name: Qwilfish Hisui
pokedex_entry: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent’s size.

name: Sneasel Hisui
pokedex_entry: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

name: Samurott Hisui
pokedex_entry: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

name: Lilligant Hisui
pokedex_entry: It’s believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant’s head to bloom.

name: Zorua Hisui
pokedex_entry: Zorua is a timid Pokémon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua’s ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

name: Zoroark Hisui
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.

name: Braviary Hisui
abilities: Keen Eye, Sheer Force, Tinted Lens
pokedex_entry: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokémon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.

name: Sliggoo Hisui
pokedex_entry: Although this Pokémon isn’t very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

name: Goodra Hisui
pokedex_entry: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don’t mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.

name: Avalugg Hisui
pokedex_entry: At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

name: Decidueye Hisui
pokedex_entry: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye’s shots never miss.

name: Dialga Origin
pokedex_entry: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

name: Palkia Origin
pokedex_entry: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

name: Basculin White Striped
pokedex_entry: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch— many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: Basculegion Female
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Enamorus Therian
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Tauros Paldea Combat Breed
pokedex_entry: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Tauros Paldea Blaze Breed
pokedex_entry: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Tauros Paldea Aqua Breed
pokedex_entry: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Wooper Paldea
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Oinkologne Female
pokedex_entry: Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.

name: Dudunsparce Three Segment
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

name: Palafin Hero
abilities: Zero To Hero, Zero To Hero
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

name: Maushold Family Of Three
pokedex_entry: The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokémon, but nobody knows for sure.

name: Tatsugiri Droopy
pokedex_entry: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

name: Tatsugiri Stretchy
pokedex_entry: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

name: Squawkabilly Blue Plumage
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Squawkabilly Yellow Plumage
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Squawkabilly White Plumage
pokedex_entry: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Gimmighoul Roaming
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

name: Koraidon Limited Build
pokedex_entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Koraidon Sprinting Build
pokedex_entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Koraidon Swimming Build
pokedex_entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Koraidon Gliding Build
pokedex_entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Miraidon Low Power Mode
pokedex_entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

name: Miraidon Drive Mode
pokedex_entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

name: Miraidon Aquatic Mode
pokedex_entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

name: Miraidon Glide Mode
pokedex_entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

name: Ursaluna Bloodmoon
pokedex_entry: No recent English description found.

name: Ogerpon Wellspring Mask
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

name: Ogerpon Hearthflame Mask
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

name: Ogerpon Cornerstone Mask
pokedex_entry: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

name: Terapagos Terastal
pokedex_entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokémon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.

name: Terapagos Stellar
pokedex_entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokémon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.
